profile_positions.description:
As a Climate Pact Ambassador, I inform, inspire and support climate action in my communities and networks by:
- Reaching out to people and/or organisations who are not yet involved in climate action;
- Informing, inspiring and supporting climate action within my communities and networks;
- Leading by example in climate action and in environmental protection;
- Bridging between civil society, interested stakeholders and the European Commission.

Manager and reporting responsibile of the XV zone of the Federazione Italiana Vela (Italian Sailing Federation - FIV) for Sport e Salute (Sport and Health) projects. 
Dissemination, organisation, and junior supervisor of joint projects between the Comitato Olimpico Nazionale Italiano (Italian National Olympic Committee - CONI) and the FIV within the framework of the grants allocated for access to the "Fund for the promotion of grassroots sports activities in the territories", will cover the following areas:
- Youth-focused and youth-led projects;
- School projects;
- Projects for the Over 65s.

Support for internal administrative tasks and external communication of the XV Zone office.

- Conceptualization of project idea “Climate Quilts” (GUST) and compiling and submitting the project application “Building transformation capacity through arts and design: Unlocking the full potential for urban transitions”; 
- Conceptualizing the project Climate Quilts: articulating its main theme, contents, relevance, timeline, work packages; 
- Identifying and communicating with anticipated projected partners in the Netherlands and Sweden;
- Guarding timely and adequate meeting of application submission deadlines, and the satisfactory supply of all necessary deliverables for the application by the project leader and partners; 
- Developing a draft of the project’s anticipated working budget with the support of advisors from Hanze; 
- Collaborated with Dr Jan van Boeckel.

The Steering Committee directs and organises the activities of the Climate Action Community of Europeana. As a member, I aim to drive impactful, cooperative and sustainable action to address the climate emergency and the environmental impact on my life, work and the digital transformation of the cultural heritage sector and I aim for wider systemic change within my organisations and networks. 

The tasks I committed to are the following: 
- Planning: through embedding eco-thinking, setting standards for managing resources, and benchmarking and measuring the Community's progress;
- Collaborating: through learning with experts, organisations and networks, harnessing my network of professionals and organisations, and sharing good practices and the challenges we encounter can empower further change at professional and organisational levels;
- Operating: through the development of a climate action strategy, meet sustainably, and cleaning up my digital practices as well as educating others on these options; 
- Advocating: through raising awareness of climate issues related to digital cultural heritage and highlighting environmentally-friendly practices on both individual and organisation levels, and providing support to other stakeholders to develop their own capacity for making sustainable change.

- Private company managing La Certosa: a state-owned island considered cultural heritage for its naturalistic and cultural-historic value in Venice;
- Responsible for the implementation and organisation of cultural projects on the island and the  relationship with an involved partner and institutions;
- Administrative Manager for special and collateral projects;
- Communication, marketing & press regarding Certosa Island with particular reference to the Marina and its complementary mooring services;
- Collaboration in the certification process within the company's quality systems with particular reference to the Marina in the ISO, Goldanchor Scheme Award, Blue Flag certifications;
- Research project "Programme for the valorisation & urban regeneration of Certosa Island": development of the valorisation programme through university research, degree theses, also in relation to the drafting of some special projects for calls for tenders; project for the valorisation of historical and archaeological research also through the creation of an exhibition space.

- CPMR Intermediterranean Commission (IMC) encompasses the issues raised in all the Regions bordering the Mediterranean Sea;
- Focus on calling for a macro-regional strategy for the Mediterranean and fostering the emergence of Mediterranean citizenship;
- The Youth Council aims to back up the IMC’s policy positions with a youth perspective, working on matters such as the environment and climate change, or social integration and Mediterranean identity;
- Responsibility to set up the regulations of the Youth Council and the relationship between its institution, the CMPR and the Regions.
